  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "alcohol-use-disorder",
  "name": "Alcohol Use Disorder - Medication Query (Naltrexone)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find AUD patients via naltrexone prescriptions. Naltrexone is also used for opioid use disorder, but it's the most disease-specific oral medication for AUD in this suite.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed naltrexone for alcohol use disorder.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on AUD medications.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed naltrexone — an opioid antagonist used for both alcohol use disorder and opioid use disorder maintenance.",
    "expert": "I need to find patients who have been prescribed naltrexone, the primary oral pharmacotherapy for alcohol use disorder. Search MedicationRequest resources for naltrexone using its RxNorm concept. Keep in mind that naltrexone is also approved for opioid use disorder, so this medication-only cohort will include patients treated for opioid dependence in addition to those with AUD — it is a useful but imprecise proxy for the alcohol use disorder population."
  },
